    "resources": [],
    "description": "RELION (for REgularised LIkelihood OptimisatioN, pronounce rely-on) is a\nstand-alone computer program that employs an empirical Bayesian approach\nto refinement of (multiple) 3D reconstructions or 2D class averages in\nelectron cryo-microscopy (cryo-EM).\n",
    "dependencies": [
        {
            "name": "cuda",
            "description": "CUDA is a parallel computing platform and programming model invented by\nNVIDIA. It enables dramatic increases in computing performance by\nharnessing the power of the graphics processing unit (GPU). Note: This\npackage does not currently install the drivers necessary to run CUDA.\nThese will need to be installed manually. See:\nhttps://docs.nvidia.com/cuda/ for details."
        },
        {
            "name": "cmake",
            "description": "A cross-platform, open-source build system. CMake is a family of tools\ndesigned to build, test and package software."
        },
        {
            "name": "mpi",
            "description": "Intel MPI Library is a multifabric message-passing library that\nimplements the open-source MPICH specification. Use the library to\ncreate, maintain, and test advanced, complex applications that perform\nbetter on high-performance computing (HPC) clusters based on Intel\nprocessors. LICENSE INFORMATION: By downloading and using this software,\nyou agree to the terms and conditions of the software license agreements\nat https://intel.ly/393CijO."
        },
        {
            "name": "fftw",
            "description": "FFTW is a C subroutine library for computing the discrete Fourier\ntransform (DFT) in one or more dimensions, of arbitrary input size, and\nof both real and complex data (as well as of even/odd data, i.e. the\ndiscrete cosine/sine transforms or DCT/DST). We believe that FFTW, which\nis free software, should become the FFT library of choice for most\napplications."
        },
        {
            "name": "fltk",
            "description": "FLTK (pronounced \"fulltick\") is a cross-platform C++ GUI toolkit for\nUNIX/Linux (X11), Microsoft Windows, and MacOS X. FLTK provides modern\nGUI functionality without the bloat and supports 3D graphics via OpenGL\nand its built-in GLUT emulation. FLTK is designed to be small and\nmodular enough to be statically linked, but works fine as a shared\nlibrary. FLTK also includes an excellent UI builder called FLUID that\ncan be used to create applications in minutes."
        },
        {
            "name": "libtiff",
            "description": "LibTIFF - Tag Image File Format (TIFF) Library and Utilities."
        },
        {
            "name": "libpng",
            "description": "libpng is the official PNG reference library."
        },
        {
            "name": "tbb",
            "description": "This is an earlier version of Intel parallel software development tools\nand has now been replaced by the Intel oneAPI Toolkits. LICENSE\nINFORMATION: By downloading and using this software, you agree to the\nterms and conditions of the software license agreements at\nhttps://intel.ly/393CijO."
        },
        {
            "name": "mkl",
            "description": "Intel Math Kernel Library. This package has been replaced by intel-\noneapi-mkl. LICENSE INFORMATION: By downloading and using this software,\nyou agree to the terms and conditions of the software license agreements\nat https://intel.ly/393CijO."
        },
        {
            "name": "ctffind",
            "description": "Fast and accurate defocus estimation from electron micrographs."
        },
        {
            "name": "motioncor2",
            "description": "MotionCor2 is a multi-GPU program that corrects beam-induced sample\nmotion recorded on dose fractionated movie stacks. It implements a\nrobust iterative alignment algorithm that delivers precise measurement\nand correction of both global and non-uniform local motions at single\npixel level, suitable for both single-particle and tomographic images.\nMotionCor2 is sufficiently fast to keep up with automated data\ncollection."
        }
